  "chapter": {
    "number": 29,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Flourishing of the Righteous"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man who remains stiff-necked after much reproof",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will suddenly be shattered beyond recovery.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When the righteous flourish, the people rejoice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but when the wicked rule, the people groan.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a companion of prostitutes squanders his wealth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By justice a king brings stability to the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a man who exacts tribute",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4265
          },
          {
            "text": "demolishes it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man who flatters his neighbor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "spreads a net for his feet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "An evil man is caught by his own sin,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a righteous one sings and rejoices.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The righteous consider the cause of the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the wicked have no regard for such concerns.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mockers inflame a city,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the wise turn away anger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If a wise man goes to court with a fool,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there will be raving and laughing with no resolution.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Men of bloodshed hate a blameless man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the upright care for his life.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4266
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A fool vents all his anger,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a wise man holds it back.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If a ruler listens to lies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all his officials will be wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The poor man and the oppressor have this in common:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD gives light to the eyes of both.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A king who judges the poor with fairness—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his throne will be established forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A rod of correction imparts wisdom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a child left to himself disgraces his mother.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When the wicked thrive, rebellion increases;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the righteous will see their downfall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Discipline your son, and he will give you rest;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he will bring delight to your soul.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where there is no vision, the people cast off restraint;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but blessed is he who keeps the Law.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A servant cannot be corrected by words alone;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though he understands, he will not respond.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you see a man who speaks in haste?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "There is more hope for a fool than for him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A servant pampered from his youth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will bring grief in the end.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "An angry man stirs up dissension,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a hot-tempered man abounds in transgression.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man’s pride will bring him low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a humble spirit will obtain honor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A partner to a thief hates his own soul;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he receives the oath, but does not testify.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fear of man is a snare,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever trusts in the LORD is set securely on high.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Many seek the ruler’s favor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a man receives justice from the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "An unjust man is detestable to the righteous,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and one whose way is upright is detestable to the wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4265,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or who taxes heavily or who takes bribes",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 29,
          "verse": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4266,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or but the upright seek his soul",
        "reference": {
